TITLE: Managing Presentation State in Reveal.js (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the `getState` and `setState` methods in Reveal.js to capture and restore the presentation's state.  `getState` returns an object containing all necessary information to revert to that specific point in the presentation. `setState` allows restoring the presentation to a previously captured state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pdfmake/docs/blob/master/themes/docdock/static/revealjs/README.md#_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
