DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to disable the default PDF compression in pdfmake by setting the 'compress' property to false within the document definition object. The 'docDefinition' object is the primary input to the pdfmake generator, and including 'compress: false' alters the output to be uncompressed. This is useful for debugging or scenarios requiring uncompressed PDF output. No external dependencies beyond pdfmake are required.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pdfmake/docs/blob/master/content/document-definition-object/compression.md#_snippet_0

